{{Infobox company | name = A.L.B Watches | logo = | company_slogan = | foundation = 2012 | founder = Vincent Candellé Tuheille & Simon-Pierre Delord | type = [[Privately held company|Private]] | location_city = Toulouse | location_country = France | key_people = | industry = Watch manufacturing | parent = | products = Luxury Watches | homepage = {{URL|alb-watches.com}} }}
'''A.L.B Watches''' is a French luxury watch brand. The company was originally called ''Atelier Le Brézéguet'', but changes its name in 2012.<ref>http://monochrome-watches.com/hot-off-the-presses-printed-watches-by-alb-watches/</ref><ref>http://additivemanufacturing.com/2014/08/15/alb-and-sculpteo-3d-printing-luxury-watches/</ref><ref>http://www.3dprinterworld.com/article/alb-watches-and-sculpteo-forging-new-horology</ref>
== Atelier Le Brézéguet ==
[[File:A.L.B Watch Model A.L.B 100.JPG|thumb|A.L.B Watch Model A.L.B 100]]
''Atelier Le Brézéguet'' refers to a locality in the Lot region of France. A.L.B workshop is based in the Toulouse area.
The founders are Vincent Candellé Tuheille & Simon-Pierre Delord, two engineers ICAM [Icam, School of Engineering]
== Partly 3D printed watches ==
A.L.B became known for its work on the field of 3D printing. The models A.L.B 000 and A.L.B 100 are among the first to integrate 3D printed dials.<ref name="The New York Times">{{cite web|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/06/fashion/watchmakers-turn-to-3-d-printing.html?_r=0|title= Watchmakers Turn to 3-D Printing|last=Siegal|first=Nina|date=November 5, 2014|publisher=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=November 5, 2014}}</ref><ref name="3dprint">{{cite web|url= http://3dprint.com/11057/alb-3d-printed-watches//|title= French Watch Designer A.L.B. Enlists Sculpteo for 3D Printing of Uniquely Beautiful Timepieces|last= Krassenstein|first= Eddie |date=August 4, 2014|publisher=3dprint|accessdate=August 4, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Sculpteo">{{cite web|url= http://www.sculpteo.com/blog/2014/07/29/3d-printing-luxury-watches-alb-sculpteo/|title= 3D printing luxury watches: ALB & Sculpteo|last=Toulmet|first=Alexia|date=July 29, 2014|publisher=[[Sculpteo]]|accessdate=July 29, 2014}}</ref>
