'''Arthur Johannes Aasland''' (22 April 1934<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=MH5lAAAAIAAJ&q=Arthur+Johannes+Aasland+22.+april+1934&dq=Arthur+Johannes+Aasland+22.+april+1934&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj8iq68v9bdAhVL6KQKHW5oDE8Q6AEIJjAB]</ref> &ndash; 17 February 2016) was a Norwegian businessperson.

He grew up in [[Luksefjell]], and took his education at the [[Norwegian Military Academy]]. After serving in the armed forces, and reaching the rank of major, he was hired in the company [[Ing. F. Selmer]] in 1963. He became director of personnel here in 1967, before working as chief executive of [[Kongsberg Våpenfabrikk]] from 1975 to 1978 and [[Løvenskiold Vækerø]] from 1979 to 1985. He then ran his own consulting firm Aasland Management, and through that served on the board of 40 companies.<ref>{{cite news|title =Arthur J. Aasland|newspaper = [[Aftenposten]]|language = no|date =2 March 2016|author=Høibak, Ralph|author2=Bye, Ronald|author3=Wabakken, Arne|page=24}}</ref>

