{{Infobox company | name = Bates Saddles | industry = Manufacturing | homepage = [https://www.batessaddles.com/] }}
'''Bates Australia''' is a leading [[saddle]] manufacturer originally established in 1934. Bates Saddlery was formed when Mr. George Bates borrowed $100 from his sister, bought a sewing machine and began to make saddles on the veranda of his home in Perth, Western Australia.<ref name="Bates Australia">[http://www.batessaddles.com.au Bates Australia<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Bates Australia is the parent company to [[Bates Saddles]] and [[Wintec]].<ref name="The Horse">[http://www.thehorse.com/ViewArticle.aspx?ID=4285 The Horse: The Right Saddle for the Job<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
The family-owned business, located in Perth, Western Australia, has expanded into many international markets and can now be found in 36 countries around the world.<ref>[http://www.tiac.wa.gov.au/sme/smx-10.htm A Snapshot of Export Activity in Western Australia's SME Sector 6Supply and Local Factors<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070831090707/http://www.tiac.wa.gov.au/sme/smx-10.htm |date=2007-08-31 }}</ref>
