{{notability|date=May 2017}} {{NPOV|date=May 2017}} {{Infobox company | name = Money.Net | logo = Money.Net black and white logo.png | logo_caption = | logo_padding = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. "fr" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{lang|[code]|[name]}}. --> | former_name = | type = | industry = Financial Data | founded = 1999<ref name="Dun and Bradstreet">{{cite web |url=https://www.dandb.com/businessdirectory/money.netincorporated-newyork-ny-16637886.html|publisher=D&B|title=D&B}}</ref><ref name="S&P Global Market Intelligence">{{cite web |url= https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=109264 |publisher= Bloomberg |title= S&P Global Market Intelligence}}</ref> | founder = Harold Louis Van Arnem IV<ref name="S&P Global Market Intelligence" /> <!-- or: | founders = --> | hq_location = | hq_location_city = New York City, NY | hq_location_country = USA | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->
| key_people = {{plainlist| * [[Morgan Downey]], [[CEO]] * [[Norman Pearlstine]] }}
| brands = | services = | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | ratio = <!-- for BANKS ONLY --> | rating = <!-- for BANKS ONLY --> | website = {{URL|http://www.money.net}} <!-- or: | homepage = --><!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Money.Net Inc''' is a privately held [[Market data|financial data]] technology company and [[financial data vendor]] based in New York City.<ref name="money">{{cite web|url=http://www.money.net/about|title=Money.Net - About|publisher=money.net|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref>
Money.Net provides [[Real-time data|real-time]] live streaming financial [[Market data|market information]] such as prices, breaking financial news, [[technical analysis software|technical analysis charts]], [[trade idea]] generation tools, and a spreadsheet API over the internet to individual [[Trader (finance)|traders]] and institutional [[Trading room|trading floors]].<ref name="businessweek">{{cite web|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=109264|title=Money.net, Inc.: Private Company Information - Businessweek|publisher=investing.businessweek.com|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref><ref name="New York Post">{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2014/10/04/ex-bloomberg-exec-challenging-terminals-with-mobile-platform/|publisher=New York Post|title=Ex-Bloomberg exec challenging terminals with mobile platform|accessdate=20 October 2014}}</ref> The product coverage is global, and is multi-asset class, including equities, fixed income, foreign exchange and commodities. It also includes reference fundamental market data such as economic statistics and corporate actions.<ref name="Irish Times">{{cite web|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/business/upstart-challenges-bloomberg-s-dominance-as-business-data-source-1.2411769|title=Upstart challenges Bloomberg’s dominance as business data source|accessdate=10 December 2015}}</ref>
The Money.Net product provides "access to real-time market data and trends for a sliver of what" traditional market data terminals cost.<ref name="Entrepreneur.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/238160|publisher=entrepreneur.com|title=An Entrepreneur Takes Aim at the Ubiquitous Bloomberg Terminal|accessdate=20 October 2014}}</ref>
Money.Net is a [[Cloud computing|cloud-based]] platform for market data. According to current CEO Morgan Downey, Money.Net has about 50,000 paying subscribers.<ref name="NY Times">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/18/business/dealbook/start-up-taking-aim-at-bloomberg-terminals-hires-former-bloomberg-head.html|publisher=The New York Times|title=Startup Taking Aim at Bloomberg Terminals Hires Former Bloomberg Head|accessdate=3 March 2017}}</ref><ref name="thefreelibrary">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Money.net+Expands+Real-Time+Streaming+Portfolio+and+Introduces...-a068991621|title=Money.net Expands Real-Time Streaming Portfolio and Introduces Premium Screamer Platinum Product. - Free Online Library|publisher=thefreelibrary.com|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.business.att.com/content/customertestimonial/moneynet.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-01-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061102134907/http://www.business.att.com/content/customertestimonial/moneynet.pdf |archivedate=2006-11-02 |df= }}</ref> It is one of the several cloud-based Financial Technology (FinTech) companies challenging dominant vendors in financial markets.<ref name="Irish Times" /> The product is available as a desktop application, via mobile devices, and through an excel spreadsheet API.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.waterstechnology.com/inside-market-data/news/2357178/moneynet-adds-etf-mutual-funds-data-bows-mobile-apps |title=Money.net adds etf, mutual funds data, bows mobile apps |publisher=Waters Technology |date= |accessdate=2014-07-30 |subscription=yes}}</ref>
In late 2016, the company announced that it had hired former Bloomberg Chief Content Officer, [[Norman Pearlstine]], to develop a new financial news division relying heavily on artificial intelligence.<ref name="NY Times">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/18/business/dealbook/start-up-taking-aim-at-bloomberg-terminals-hires-former-bloomberg-head.html|publisher=The New York Times|title=Startup Taking Aim at Bloomberg Terminals Hires Former Bloomberg Head|accessdate=3 March 2017}}</ref>
